alembicio = zero-downtime embedding model migration orchestrator. INVARIANTS.md and
DESIGN.md in the repo root are binding; consult them before non-trivial changes. The
condensed law:

- Exactly-once EFFECTS via idempotency key (doc_id, content_hash, target_model_id);
  all vector writes are idempotent upserts; replays must be no-ops (I1).
- Progress markers commit only after the writes they cover are durable; markers are
  monotonic (I2). Deletes always win (I3). Updates mark rows dirty via content_hash;
  stale writes never satisfy a dirty row (I4).
- Budget counters are monotone, persisted, enforced pre-spend; exhaustion lands in
  PAUSED_BUDGET at a batch boundary, resumable (I5).
- Only state transitions listed in DESIGN.md §2; every CLI verb idempotent (I6). Reads
  are never mixed-space within one query (I7). Mapping mode: provenance="projected",
  gated on measured held-out recovery, always overwritten by true embeddings (I8).
- Engineering conventions (I12): output ENTIRE files when modifying; no TODO / no `...`
  / no placeholder comments — every function complete and runnable; never rename or
  break released public symbols; new params keyword-only with defaults; type
  annotations on every signature; docstrings (summary + Args/Returns) on public
  methods; mapping/ and eval/metrics are NumPy-only (no scipy/sklearn/torch in core).
- Never weaken, skip, or delete failing tests to get green (I13).
- Secrets only via env: indirection; destructive verbs dry-run by default (I11).
